### SystemMonitor API — VS Code REST Client
### Install "REST Client" extension, then click "Send Request" above any request

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@contentType = application/json

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HEALTH
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Liveness check
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/health/live

### Readiness check (checks Cosmos + Service Bus)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/health/ready

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SCHEMA NORMALIZATION — test the core feature
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Test a single attribute name resolution
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/schema/resolve/test
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "rawName": "CPU %"
}

###

### Test with a renamed attribute (simulates customer config change)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/schema/resolve/test
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "rawName": "processorUsage"
}

###

### Test with something completely unknown
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/schema/resolve/test
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "rawName": "some_totally_new_metric_xyz"
}

###

### Bulk test — paste your customer's new attribute names here
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/schema/resolve/bulk-test
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "rawNames": [
    "cpu_percent",
    "CPU %",
    "processorUsage",
    "cpu usage",
    "CPU Utilization (%)",
    "Processor(_Total)\\% Processor Time",
    "memory_percent",
    "mem usage",
    "MemUsage",
    "RAM %",
    "Available MBytes",
    "disk_write_mbps",
    "DiskWriteBytes",
    "WriteBytesPerSec",
    "Full Name",
    "something_unknown_xyz"
  ]
}

###

### Get all canonical attributes
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/schema/canonical

###

### Get unknown attributes pending review
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/schema/unknown

###

### Get unknown attribute stats
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/schema/unknown/stats

###

### Add a new alias to an existing canonical attribute
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/schema/canonical/cpu_percent/aliases
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "alias": "my_custom_cpu_name"
}

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# INGESTION
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Ingest metrics with canonical names (normal flow)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ingest/metrics
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "events": [
    {
      "agentId": "test-agent-001",
      "hostName": "web-server-01",
      "environment": "development",
      "type": "System",
      "values": {
        "cpu_percent": 72.4,
        "memory_percent": 61.2,
        "error_rate": 0.02,
        "p99_latency_ms": 245
      }
    }
  ]
}

###

### Ingest metrics with RENAMED attributes (tests normalization)
### This simulates a customer upgrading their config
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ingest/metrics
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "events": [
    {
      "agentId": "test-agent-001",
      "hostName": "web-server-01",
      "environment": "development",
      "type": "System",
      "values": {
        "processorUsage": 72.4,
        "RAM %": 61.2,
        "error_rate": 0.02,
        "ResponseTimeP99": 245,
        "a_brand_new_unknown_metric": 99.9
      }
    }
  ]
}

###

### Ingest an anomalous metric (should trigger alert)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ingest/metrics
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "events": [
    {
      "agentId": "test-agent-001",
      "hostName": "web-server-01",
      "environment": "development",
      "type": "System",
      "values": {
        "cpu_percent": 97.8,
        "memory_percent": 94.1,
        "error_rate": 0.45,
        "p99_latency_ms": 4200
      }
    }
  ]
}

###

### Ingest logs
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ingest/logs
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "events": [
    {
      "agentId": "test-agent-001",
      "hostName": "web-server-01",
      "serviceName": "payments-api",
      "environment": "development",
      "level": "Error",
      "message": "Database connection timeout after 30s"
    },
    {
      "agentId": "test-agent-001",
      "hostName": "web-server-01",
      "serviceName": "payments-api",
      "environment": "development",
      "level": "Information",
      "message": "Request processed in 142ms"
    }
  ]
}

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ANALYTICS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Dashboard summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/summary

###

### Recent anomalies (last 60 min)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/anomalies?offsetMinutes=60&limit=20

###

### Critical anomalies only
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/anomalies?minSeverity=Critical&offsetMinutes=60

###

### Agent health scores
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/health

###

### Metric time series (replace agentId with one from your running agents)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/metrics/mock-agent-001/cpu_percent?windowMinutes=30

###

### Infrastructure status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/infrastructure
